  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "In contrast to the task adapter, the dialect adapter is trained to output standard dialect representations for an input text.",
    "Hence, LORDD stacks the task adapter on top of the dialect adapter (as shown in Figure 2), allowing the models to predict the target word as required for TWP.",
    "We experiment with two open-weight decoder models namely, Mistral-7B-Instruct-v0.2 (MISTRAL; Jiang et al., 2023) and Gemma2-9B-Instruct (GEMMA; Gemma Team, 2024).",
    "LORDD is trained as follows:",
    "• The task adapter is trained by fine-tuning the model for 20 epochs, with a batch size of 32, Paged 8-bit AdamW (Dettmers et al., 2022) as the optimiser and learning rate of 2e-4."
  ],
